<div type="definition">
<p>INTERACT with FOR one's SELF:own AIMS.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word is yòng 用 (ant. fèi 廢 "give up the use of, not use").</p>
<p>2. Yǐ 以 refers to the use of things as instruments for a given purpose and rarely involves the using up of resources.</p>
<p>3. Shǐ 使 refers to the deployment of what one controls with no special emphasis on the purpose.</p>
<p>4. Jiā 加 refers to the deployment or application of something in the course of some action.</p>
        </div>
